[[File:Daclif_Gallamby.jpg|thumb|right|220px|[[Daclif Gallamby]], the last Diktat of Corellia]]
{{Quote|The New Republic didn't want to arrest him. After all, the Diktat was the legal head of government.|[[Leia Organa Solo/Legends|Leia Organa Solo]]|<ref name="AaC">''[[Ambush at Corellia]]''</ref>}}
'''Diktat''' was the title held by the [[Head of State/Legends|head of state]] of [[Corellia/Legends|Corellia]] following the the abolition of the [[Corellian empire]]. The title was used during centuries but disappeared with the fall of the last Diktat, [[Daclif Gallamby]], near the end of the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]].

==Description==
{{Quote|Please be courteous to the Diktat. He's a powerful man.|[[Lieutenant/Legends|Lieutenant]] [[Mack Jasper|Jasper]], to a spacer|<ref name="SWG:StDO">{{SWGcite|exp=NGE|type=general|Search the Diktat's Office|Corellia}}</ref>}}
The Diktat was the elected executive of the government of the [[Corellian republic|republic of Corellia]]. This individual was therefore responsible for the direct administration of the planet. In addition, the Diktat also served as [[Governor-General/Legends|Governor-General]] of the [[Corellian sector/Legends|Corellian sector]] and, consequently, as the [[Commander-in-Chief/Legends|commander-in-chief]] of the [[Corellian Defense Force/Legends|Corellian Defense Force]] and [[Director/Legends|director]] of the [[Corellian Security Force]].<ref name="SoF">''[[Suns of Fortune]]''</ref>

[[File:CoronetCapitol.jpg|thumb|left|250px|The [[Coronet Capitol]], the siege of the Office of the Diktat]]
Although the Diktat was the formal head-of-state of a constitutional monarchy, the regime had somehow evolved to a corporatocracy led by the boards of directors of the most powerful Corellian corporations, including [[Corellian Engineering Corporation/Legends|Corellian Engineering Corporation]], [[Corellia Mining Corporation/Legends|Corellia Mining Corporation]] and [[Gowix Computers]]. As such, the real power of the Diktat depended on the corporate powers managing the government, with some Diktats only serving as puppets on Corellia while other actively ruled the entire sector.<ref name="SoF" /> In any case, the duties of the Diktat included maximizing Corellia's footprint in shipbuilding and interstellar trade.<ref name="TEA">''[[The Essential Atlas]]''</ref>

The Diktat and its administration had their office in the [[Coronet Capitol]],<ref name="SWG:StDO" /> in the [[Governmental Sector]] of [[Coronet City/Legends|Coronet City]], Corellia. The Diktat resided in the majestic thousand-year-old [[Corona House/Legends|Corona House]], the former residence of the [[King/Legends|monarchs]] of Corellia.<ref name="SoF" />

The Corellian Diktat could award the [[Medal for Distinguished Service]].<ref name="SWG:RtToaGD">{{SWGcite|exp=NGE|type=general|Receive the Thanks of a Grateful Diktat|Corellia}}</ref>

==History==
{{Quote|The Corellian leaders stopped trusting their own people, and put more and more of the same sort of restrictions on them. And with the Imperial government propping up the Corellian Diktat&mdash;that's what they called their chief of state&mdash;the Diktat could do whatever he wanted without any fear of the people protesting.|Leia Organa Solo|<ref name="AaC" />}}
The title of Diktat was created along with the establishment of a republic on Corellia following the dissolution of [[Corellian empire]] by its last king, [[Berethron e Solo]],<ref name="SoF" /> in [[312 BBY]].<ref name="TEA" /> In the next centuries, many of the individuals who held this title died under suspicious circumstances.<ref name="AaS">''[[Assault at Selonia]]''</ref>

In the last years of the [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Galactic Republic]], a woman named [[Shyla Merricope]] served as Diktat. During the [[Separatist Crisis/Legends|Separatist Crisis]], Diktat Merricope and [[Senator/Legends|Senator]] [[Garm Bel Iblis/Legends|Garm Bel Iblis]] invoked ''[[Contemplanys Hermi]]'' to temporary withdraw the Corellian sector from the Galactic Republic and prevent the coming [[Clone Wars/Legends|Clone Wars]] from harming the sector.<ref name="HNN47">{{HoloNetNewsWeb|47|news/13314_1.html|Corellia Closes Borders}}</ref>

At the time of the [[Declaration of a New Order]], when the Galactic Republic transitioned into the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]], the Corellian Diktat was [[Dupas Thomree]]. Thomree made an arrangement with [[Galactic Emperor/Legends|Emperor]] [[Palpatine/Legends|Palpatine]] to maintain his regime and the independence of the Corellian sector.<ref name="TFUCG">''[[The Force Unleashed Campaign Guide]]''</ref> Hence, the sector became an [[Imperial client state]].<ref name="SoF" /> Dupas Thomree accepted to support Imperial galactic policies, pay taxes to the Empire and maintain the activity of the [[CEC shipyards|Corellian shipyards]]<ref name="TFUCG" /> to produce Imperial [[Warship/Legends|warships]].<ref name="TEGtW">''[[The Essential Guide to Warfare]]''</ref> The Corellian sector remained officially independent and the Diktat saved its government but he became a puppet ruler who only controlled the administration of the planet Corellia. Although the Corellian Diktat kept the title of Governor-General of the Corellian sector, the sector and its Corellian Defense Force were ''de facto'' placed under the authority of the newly-appointed [[Grand Moff/Legends|Grand Moff]] of the Corellian sector.<ref name="SoF" /> Indeed, this situation led the independent-minded people of Corellia to protests vigorously against the Diktat.<ref name="TFUCG" /> Over time, Diktat Dupas Thomree distanced himself from his populations and increased restrictions on freedom. With the full support and protection of the Empire, the Diktat became an autocrat who could do whatever he wanted without any concern of the population protesting. Moreover, the position of Diktat became a lifetime appointment; with each Diktat selecting himself his successor.<ref name="AaS" /> In the meantime, [[Imperial Security Bureau/Legends|Imperial Security Bureau]] and [[Commission for the Preservation of the New Order/Legends|COMPNOR]] agents infiltrated the Corellian society to ensure the Diktat respected his deal with the Emperor but also to eliminate any threat to the Diktat rule.<ref name="TFUCG" />

When the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]] erupted between the Galactic Empire and the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebel Alliance]], Diktat Dupas Thomree accepted to provide Corellian military forces to the Empire. Dupas Thomree died not long after and was replaced by his designated successor, [[Daclif Gallamby]], who was completely unknown to the public.<ref name="AaS" /> During Gallamby's rule, the Galactic Civil War intensified. As Corellian armed forces were repeatedly sent away to support the Empire against the Rebellion, [[Pirate/Legends|piracy]] exploded in the Corellian sector and the local economy began to decline. After the Rebel victory at the [[Battle of Yavin/Legends|Battle of Yavin]], the Diktat and his government became paranoid<ref name="CTD">''[[Cracken's Threat Dossier]]''</ref> and got scared to be overthrown by the Rebellion or by their own population.<ref name="AaC" /> Eventually, the Corellian government enacted strict isolationist measures, restricting trade and traffic<ref name="CTD" /> throughout the entire sector. These measures caused the collapse of the Corellian economy.<ref name="AaC" /> Sometime during the reign of the Empire, an [[Aro-GX Security Droid]] reprogrammed by Corellian criminals almost assassinating the Diktat.<ref name="CFTD">''[[Cynabar's Fantastic Technology: Droids]]''</ref> In [[1 ABY/Legends|1 ABY]],<ref name="SWG_timeline">{{SWG_timeline}}</ref> a band of criminals known as the [[Rogue CorSec]] attempted to overthrow Diktat Daclif Gallamby but their plot was foiled by the Corellian Security Force.<ref name="SWG:GttSotRS">{{SWGcite|exp=NGE|type=general|Go to the Source of the Remote Signal|Corellia}}</ref>

After the death of the Emperor at the [[Battle of Endor/Legends|Battle of Endor]] in [[4 ABY/Legends|4 ABY]], the Galactic Empire fragmented.<ref name="TEA" /> At first, Diktat Gallamby's position was strengthened by the massive arrival of Imperial officers and troops who sought to take refuge in the Corellian sector.<ref name="XW:RS">''[[X-Wing: Rogue Squadron]]''</ref> However, without the direct protection of the Emperor, the Diktat's government flickered. The resentful Corellian population protested more and more vehemently<ref name="CTD" /> and the Diktat gradually lost power to the [[Sacorrian Triad]].<ref name="CatCW">''[[Coruscant and the Core Worlds]]''</ref> In [[7 ABY/Legends|7 ABY]], the Diktat dissolved the prestigious Corellian Security Force and allocated most of its resources to the new [[Public Safety Service]],<ref name="XW:WG">''[[X-Wing: Wedge's Gamble]]''</ref> an Imperialistic security force and political police tasked with protecting the regime.<ref name="IJ">''[[I, Jedi]]''</ref> However, as early as [[13 ABY/Legends|13 ABY]],<ref name="XW:SoA">''[[X-Wing: Starfighters of Adumar]]''</ref> the Diktat's regime fell apart. As the population revolted, the Corellian armed forces<ref name="AaS" /> and security forces eventually stopped to protect the government.<ref name="AaC" /> Daclif Gallamby and his supporters soon grabbed half the credits in the state treasury and fled the Corellian system. Due to the sudden disappearance of the Diktat, his presumed successor, [[Thrackan Sal-Solo]], was not able to prevent the regime to collapse.<ref name="AaS" /> The Corellian administration remained in disarray until the [[New Republic/Legends|New Republic]] gained control of the Corellian sector and appointed a Governor-General to rule the planet Corellia and the sector.<ref name="CTD" />

[[File:ThrackanSalSoloHS-NEGTC.png|thumb|right|220px|[[Thrackan Sal-Solo]], self-proclaimed Diktat of Corellia]]
In [[18 ABY/Legends|18 ABY]], during the [[Corellian Crisis]], the Corellian separatists of the [[Human League]] assassinated Governor-General [[Micamberlecto]] and seized control of Corellia. Their leader, Thrackan Sal-Solo, proclaimed himself the new Diktat of Corellia with the objective to re-establish the previous regime.<ref name="AaS" /> However, Sal-Solo's reign was short-lived. He was arrested by the New Republic at the end of the Corellian Crisis, therefore restoring the authority of the New Republic over Corellia.<ref name="CTD" />

Thrackan Sal-Solo was imprisoned for years after the conclusion of the Corellian Crisis but he was freed prematurely by the New Republic in exchange for his help in the [[Yuuzhan Vong War|war]] against the [[Yuuzhan Vong]].<ref name="TNEGtC">''[[The New Essential Guide to Characters]]''</ref> Sal-Solo became a war hero for the Corellians during the [[Battle of Fondor]]. He later returned to politics and was elected Governor-General of the Corellian sector in [[26 ABY/Legends|26 ABY]].<ref name="Recovery">''[[The New Jedi Order: Recovery]]''</ref> From this position, Thrackan Sal-Solo attempted to betray the New Republic and get the support of the Yuuzhan Vong in order to declare the independence of the Corellian sector and proclaimed himself Diktat. Ironically, Sal-Solo was betrayed by the Yuuzhan Vong who were not interested in the proposal.<ref name="Ylesia">''[[The New Jedi Order: Ylesia]]''</ref>

The title of Diktat, as well as the title Governor-General of the Corellian sector, disappeared definitively after the Corellians established a new political regime, the [[Five Worlds]], prior to the [[Second Galactic Civil War]].<ref name="Betrayal">''[[Legacy of the Force: Betrayal]]''</ref>

